                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_249A-item1">
                     <author key="n80115655" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/2474895/">Niẓāmī Ganjavī, 1140 or 41-1202 or 3نظامى گنجوى</author>
                     <author>Shaikh Muhammad b. Fakhr al-Din Ahmad al-Katib al-Sultani.</author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Iskandar-namah.</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en">Contains both parts of the work.</title>
                     <note>The entry is written in ink in the Library copy of Codrington. A folio (unnumbered) before f1a has on the verso a panel of illumination above the beginning of the Timur-namah of Hatifi. The recto is covered with verses. The manuscript has suffered from damp and wear. It was conserved in 1964 by Roger Powell; the details of his extensive repair work are noted in typed page inserted at the end of the MS. Repaired in 1964 details of repair pasted in MS last page.</note>
                     <incipit>Incipit, part 1 (a replacement): Khudaya jahanpadshahi turast Incipit, part 2: Khirad har kuja ganji arad padid</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 246.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
